cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CR 

The paper focuses on person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the usage of Deep Decompositional Network and Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) features, which are related to machine learning and deep learning, respectively. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the usage of similarity learning and ranking aggregation, which are related to information retrieval and data mining. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a post-ranking approach to improve initial ranking lists, which is related to computer security. Hence, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
